# ━━━ LEARN ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# .env.example is a TEMPLATE for environment variables.
# It is committed to Git so new developers know which variables
# they need to configure. The actual .env file is gitignored.
#
# Workflow:
#   1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in your actual values
#   3. Never commit .env — only .env.example
#
# Compare with ASP.NET: This is like appsettings.json, but for
# secrets. In ASP.NET you might use User Secrets or Azure Key
# Vault; here, .env files are the standard for local development.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Application
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
APP_NAME=DevBrain
APP_ENV=development
DEBUG=true

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend (FastAPI)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BACKEND_PORT=8000
BACKEND_HOST=0.0.0.0
BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend (Next.js)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=DevBrain

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database (PostgreSQL)
# The connection string format is:
#   postgresql+asyncpg://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POSTGRES_USER=devbrain
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=devbrain_secret
POSTGRES_DB=devbrain
POSTGRES_HOST=localhost
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://devbrain:devbrain_secret@localhost:5432/devbrain

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Redis
# Used for: Celery broker, LiteLLM caching, session cache
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI Providers (via LiteLLM)
#
# LEARN: LiteLLM is an abstraction layer that provides a unified
# API for multiple LLM providers. You configure each provider's
# API key here, and LiteLLM handles routing and fallback.
#
# All providers below have FREE tiers:
# - Google AI Studio: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# - Groq: https://console.groq.com/keys
# - HuggingFace: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Primary: Google AI Studio (gemma-4-31b-it + text-embedding-005)
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Fallback LLM: Groq (llama-3.3-70b-versatile)
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# Fallback Embeddings: HuggingFace (BAAI/bge-m3)
HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=your_huggingface_api_key_here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Authentication (Auth.js v5)
# Generate a secret: openssl rand -base64 32
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AUTH_SECRET=your_auth_secret_here

# GitHub OAuth
# Create app: https://github.com/settings/applications/new
AUTH_GITHUB_ID=your_github_client_id
AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET=your_github_client_secret

# Google OAuth
# Create app: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
AUTH_GOOGLE_ID=your_google_client_id
AUTH_GOOGLE_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
